About the Class!
  MBAI 5400G Visualization and Storytelling is a 5th-year course in Ontario Tech University taught by Professor Gabby Resch. 
The course discusses the way data can be turned into powerful visual stories that can inform, persuade and resonate with 
audiences. During the semester, we have learned such important issues as the principles of data visualization, technique of 
storytelling, design thinking, and interactive web-based visualizations. Prof. Resch was confident and creative in all 
classes, as she made students go beyond normal charts and reflect on how visuals convey meaning. The best aspects of the 
course were learning to tell stories using data, and creating visualizations that simplify complex information. Since I am
studying data analytics and business analysis as a career, the course provided me with communication skills to complement
my technical background to understand that the most effective analysts are not only those who can derive insights in data, 
but those who can also communicate and make other people interested in them.


Thank You prof Gabby Resch🙏.
